    <FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>How to: Style a Content Control</Run>

              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

      <Paragraph><Run Foreground="DarkGray">[The content included in this documentation is a sub-set of the Windows SDK, and may not be complete or current. Please see the online Windows SDK for current documentation.]</Run>

      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph/>
      <Paragraph/>
      <Paragraph>A ContentControl has a very limited default style therefore it has a simple visual appearance. If an application writer wishes he can create a visual appearance for a content control by making a template or style and applying it to the control. This example creates a template and a style which are applied to content controls.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example    
      </Paragraph>

      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>XAML </Run>

              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New" xml:space="preserve"><Run>
&lt;Style x:Key="ContentCtrl" TargetType="{x:Type ContentControl}"> 
&lt;Setter Property="Foreground" Value="Green"/> 
&lt;Setter Property="FontSize" Value="20"/> 
&lt;Setter Property="FontWeight" Value="Bold"/> 
&lt;Setter Property="Template"> 
&lt;Setter.Value> 
&lt;ControlTemplate TargetType="{x:Type ContentControl}"> 
&lt;ContentControl ContentControl.Content="Hello"/> 
&lt;/ControlTemplate> 
&lt;/Setter.Value> 
&lt;/Setter> 
&lt;/Style> </Run>
            
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

      <Paragraph><Run/>
      </Paragraph>

      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph>Note:             
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph> For the complete code sample see Content Control Sample.            
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

